The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Fuller Acres had a population of 917. The population density was {{convert|1,216.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Fuller Acres was 211 (23.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 35 (3.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2 (0.2%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 1 (0.1%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 507 (55.3%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 159 (17.3%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 769 persons (83.9%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Fuller Acres CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0627190 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 232 households, out of which 105 (45.3%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 129 (55.6%) were married-couple households, 17 (7.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 51 (22.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 35 (15.1%) had a male householder with no partner present. 25 households (10.8%) were one person, and 11 (4.7%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 3.95.<ref name=DP1/> There were 193 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (83.2% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Fuller Acres CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0627190 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 292 people (31.8%) under the age of 18, 78 people (8.5%) aged 18 to 24, 225 people (24.5%) aged 25 to 44, 223 people (24.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 99 people (10.8%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 33.1{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 105.1 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 248 housing units at an average density of {{convert|328.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 232 (93.5%) were occupied. Of these, 100 (43.1%) were owner-occupied, and 132 (56.9%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

